1
00:01:09,520 --> 00:01:12,640
One more shot please. One, two, three.

2
00:01:13,360 --> 00:01:15,560
Beautiful. Thank you.

3
00:01:18,840 --> 00:01:21,800
Marriage means you're no longer alone.

4
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:24,040
Whatever you do,

5
00:01:24,600 --> 00:01:26,800
{\an8}always think of the other person.

6
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:31,040
{\an8}I wish you both happiness.

7
00:01:40,440 --> 00:01:42,600
Take good care of Fun for me.

8
00:01:45,160 --> 00:01:47,720
- Yes.
- If things get tough,

9
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:48,840
please forgive each other.

10
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:52,760
Marriage is just the beginning
of a shared life.

11
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:54,720
Some days will be happy,

12
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:56,320
{\an8}some will be sad.

13
00:01:57,320 --> 00:02:00,680
Sometimes, you'll be angry
or upset with each other.

14
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:04,400
Just don't let it go too far.

15
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:08,000
I wish you happiness.

16
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:09,560
Thank you.

17
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:17,560
A happy marriage

18
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:20,960
needs a good standard of life.

19
00:02:21,040 --> 00:02:22,960
The house must be clean

20
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:24,200
and hygienic.

21
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:27,880
Food should be proper and of good quality,

22
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:29,720
and delicious too.

23
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:33,760
Fun, you need to practice.
You need to learn more.

24
00:02:35,320 --> 00:02:36,320
Yes.

25
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:39,320
Mom.

26
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:41,920
Oh.

27
00:02:43,920 --> 00:02:44,960
Well,

28
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:48,560
I wish you both happiness then.

29
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:54,560
- And--
- Me too.

30
00:02:54,640 --> 00:02:57,760
I also wish you both lots of happiness.

31
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:02,040
Alright, that's everyone.
The ceremony is complete.

32
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:05,800
Let's leave the two of them be.

33
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:07,960
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

34
00:03:08,040 --> 00:03:09,000
Of course.

35
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:10,760
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

36
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:11,800
Return the wai.

37
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:30,880
Your blessing was very impressive.

38
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:34,840
You spoke just like
a truly kind and virtuous elder.

39
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:42,200
I'll take my leave now.

40
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:47,880
Calm down.

41
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:49,120
Priaw.

42
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:52,720
You heard that, right? She insulted me.

43
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:55,440
Come on, go easy, Auntie.

44
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:57,280
I am.

45
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:58,600
Well.

46
00:03:58,680 --> 00:04:01,440
It's not like I'm pleased about it.

47
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:04,280
But I don't want any problems with Oon.

48
00:04:06,440 --> 00:04:08,160
Your daughter loves her.

49
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:12,400
The car's waiting downstairs. Let's go.
I'll lock up the house for Oon.

50
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:14,320
Fine. Let's go.

51
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:16,519
Calm down.

52
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:21,120
Don't go down too fast, Priaw.

53
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:22,400
Yeah, I know.

54
00:04:22,480 --> 00:04:24,320
- I don't want to run into them.
- Yeah, let's go.

55
00:04:32,960 --> 00:04:35,240
- Are you tired?
- Not at all.

56
00:04:35,320 --> 00:04:37,080
I'm very, very happy.

57
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:41,720
Let's take some selfies,
to have them as memories.

58
00:05:14,640 --> 00:05:15,600
Come here.

59
00:05:25,960 --> 00:05:27,000
Thank you.

60
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:28,240
Here, let me help you.

61
00:05:30,240 --> 00:05:31,560
Done.

62
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:32,720
Thank you.

63
00:05:38,440 --> 00:05:41,000
I'll help you take off your dress.

64
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:25,320
Oon, no, the dress will tear.

65
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:29,760
It won't.

66
00:07:08,520 --> 00:07:10,200
Let's shower first.

67
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:12,520
We can shower later.

68
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:16,160
No, take a shower first.
It's been since this morning.

69
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:21,360
The bathroom…

70
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:24,360
Alright, let's shower first.

71
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:04,520
It's hard to believe
we made it to this day.

72
00:08:06,840 --> 00:08:09,360
Do you remember the first day we met?

73
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:14,280
Of course. I remember everything.

74
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:26,240
Thank you

75
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:29,480
for making me
the happiest person in the world.

76
00:08:34,039 --> 00:08:34,919
No.

77
00:08:35,559 --> 00:08:38,600
I'm the lucky one.

78
00:08:42,640 --> 00:08:43,799
I love you.

79
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:46,840
I love you too.

80
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:20,240
Morning.

81
00:11:27,560 --> 00:11:28,680
Morning.

82
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:31,320
No.

83
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:39,200
We have to get up now.
We have a mission today.

84
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:40,600
A mission?

85
00:12:41,920 --> 00:12:43,000
What mission?

86
00:12:43,080 --> 00:12:45,960
The wedding's already over.

87
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:48,680
I even took the day off.

88
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:50,840
What are we doing?

89
00:12:52,360 --> 00:12:55,600
Our mission is to open the presents.

90
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:01,240
The great mission.

91
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:03,760
Of course.

92
00:13:16,040 --> 00:13:18,000
But before any mission,

93
00:13:18,080 --> 00:13:19,720
we need to refuel first.

94
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:27,240
Here.

95
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:28,760
Thank you.

96
00:13:39,440 --> 00:13:40,840
Go ahead, eat.

97
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:28,760
You can start opening them first.

98
00:14:28,840 --> 00:14:31,560
I'll take care of the dishes.

99
00:14:31,640 --> 00:14:32,880
Do you want to do it together?

100
00:14:32,960 --> 00:14:34,560
There are gifts from your friends too.

101
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:35,600
I can wait.

102
00:14:37,160 --> 00:14:40,960
They're our gifts.
What's mine is yours too.

103
00:14:41,760 --> 00:14:45,040
Go ahead. I'll enjoy watching from here.

104
00:14:45,880 --> 00:14:47,280
Thank you.

105
00:15:06,680 --> 00:15:08,000
A vase?

106
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:12,560
Wow.

107
00:15:13,800 --> 00:15:16,760
A tea set. It's so pretty.

108
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:44,800
Did you just move in?

109
00:15:44,880 --> 00:15:46,360
Uh, yes.

110
00:15:46,440 --> 00:15:49,600
{\an8}I'm Aunt Chawee.
You can just call me Aunt Wi.

111
00:15:49,680 --> 00:15:54,320
Alright, Aunt Wi.
My name is Aioon. Nice to meet you.

112
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:55,560
What was your name again?

113
00:15:55,640 --> 00:15:56,600
Aioon.

114
00:15:56,680 --> 00:15:57,640
Aioon?

115
00:15:59,840 --> 00:16:00,680
Hey,

116
00:16:00,760 --> 00:16:05,440
if you ever need anything
or have any problems, let me know.

117
00:16:05,520 --> 00:16:08,000
We're neighbors, after all, okay?

118
00:16:08,080 --> 00:16:09,720
Shall we exchange contact numbers?

119
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:12,000
I didn't bring my phone.

120
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:15,120
Just tell me your ID.
I'll type it in. I'm very fast.

121
00:16:15,200 --> 00:16:16,960
I'd better type it for you. It's long.

122
00:16:17,040 --> 00:16:19,640
I'm good at typing. Just tell me.

123
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:21,760
Gxcvbnm79.

124
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:23,880
You type it, dear.

125
00:16:23,960 --> 00:16:24,800
Sure.

126
00:16:25,640 --> 00:16:27,040
I'll type it for you.

127
00:16:29,760 --> 00:16:31,680
- There, done.
- Alright, I'll add you.

128
00:16:31,760 --> 00:16:35,160
I'll head back inside now.
I still have things to unpack.

129
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:37,600
Oh, okay. Don't forget.

130
00:16:37,680 --> 00:16:40,400
You can message me anytime, 24/7.
I'm always happy to help.

131
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:44,360
Goodbye.

132
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:56,360
Pa, come here.

133
00:16:56,440 --> 00:16:57,360
- Hurry.
- What?

134
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:58,600
I've got something to update you on.

135
00:16:58,680 --> 00:17:00,440
Guess what it is.

136
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:01,480
What's on your face?

137
00:17:01,560 --> 00:17:02,400
Hey!

138
00:17:03,120 --> 00:17:05,440
Don't touch my lucky beauty mark.

139
00:17:06,440 --> 00:17:09,920
{\an8}You just stuck something on your face.
I thought it was tapioca from bubble tea.

140
00:17:10,560 --> 00:17:12,160
You're underestimating it.

141
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:14,839
This is the highest level
of fashion in this neighborhood.

142
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:16,440
So what's the update?

143
00:17:16,520 --> 00:17:17,560
Yeah.

144
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:20,359
I met our new neighbor.

145
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:23,319
Her name is Aioon.
But I didn't see her husband.

146
00:17:23,400 --> 00:17:26,720
Auntie, if you want to be nosy,
keep your voice down.

147
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:27,839
- Was I loud?
- Yes.

148
00:17:27,920 --> 00:17:29,480
Sorry.

149
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:32,720
And how do you know
she even has a husband?

150
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:35,480
Well, I heard it from a high-level source.

151
00:17:35,560 --> 00:17:38,920
The workers who built the house
said it's a bridal home.

152
00:17:39,520 --> 00:17:41,720
But I think they're a female couple.

153
00:17:42,920 --> 00:17:44,120
Last night,

154
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:46,640
I saw two brides getting out of the car.

155
00:17:46,720 --> 00:17:50,040
What? You had that kind of info
and didn't tell me?

156
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:12,480
Why did you take so long?

157
00:18:12,560 --> 00:18:16,400
A neighbor came over to say hello,
so I stopped to chat.

158
00:18:16,480 --> 00:18:19,200
- A neighbor?
- Mm, yes.

159
00:18:19,280 --> 00:18:22,600
An auntie who lives next door.

160
00:18:22,680 --> 00:18:23,840
Oh, I see.

161
00:18:25,200 --> 00:18:27,720
Hey, Oon-oon, you got a message.

162
00:18:36,160 --> 00:18:38,840
Fun, what day is it today?

163
00:18:41,280 --> 00:18:43,760
Tuesday.

164
00:18:44,560 --> 00:18:48,640
You know, I've already gotten

165
00:18:48,720 --> 00:18:50,440
two "Happy Tuesday" messages today.

166
00:18:50,520 --> 00:18:51,360
{\an8}HAPPY TUESDAY

167
00:18:54,880 --> 00:18:55,800
That's lovely.

168
00:18:58,280 --> 00:19:01,480
Are you going to reply?

169
00:19:01,560 --> 00:19:02,760
Good question.

170
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:06,880
I'll find one of those messages
my mom used to send and reply with that.

171
00:20:01,280 --> 00:20:03,880
Can you give me a minute?
I need to finish some work

172
00:20:03,960 --> 00:20:05,640
before I send it to--

173
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:22,000
Where?

174
00:20:23,640 --> 00:20:24,520
Here?

175
00:20:33,240 --> 00:20:34,440
Here?

176
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:38,520
Or…

177
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:42,560
here?

178
00:20:57,800 --> 00:21:00,880
Anywhere, just not here.

179
00:21:01,480 --> 00:21:03,360
Okay. Not here.

180
00:21:04,240 --> 00:21:08,200
Hey, Aioon. No, stop playing.

181
00:21:08,280 --> 00:21:11,240
- I'm not playing. I'm serious.
- Stop.

182
00:21:12,520 --> 00:21:13,840
<i>Fun.</i>

183
00:21:15,480 --> 00:21:17,200
Still not ready yet?

184
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:54,360
You look beautiful.

185
00:22:05,280 --> 00:22:07,200
I have nothing to wear.

186
00:22:07,280 --> 00:22:08,480
Huh?

187
00:22:09,680 --> 00:22:11,920
Nothing to wear?

188
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:13,360
Yes.

189
00:22:13,440 --> 00:22:15,680
Then what are all these?

190
00:22:15,760 --> 00:22:17,360
And these?

191
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:19,000
These aren't clothes?

192
00:22:20,880 --> 00:22:22,800
Well, I've gained weight.

193
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:24,640
Some are too big,

194
00:22:24,720 --> 00:22:26,400
some are too small,

195
00:22:26,960 --> 00:22:29,600
and some I've worn too often.

196
00:22:29,680 --> 00:22:31,040
Like…

197
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:33,040
this one.

198
00:22:35,160 --> 00:22:36,560
And some

199
00:22:37,800 --> 00:22:39,720
that you haven't even worn yet.

200
00:22:43,440 --> 00:22:44,400
Did I buy those?

201
00:22:44,480 --> 00:22:47,240
Yes, you did. Two bags.

202
00:22:47,320 --> 00:22:49,200
Oon-oon, did you hide my clothes?

203
00:22:49,280 --> 00:22:51,000
Me? Hide them?

204
00:22:51,080 --> 00:22:53,160
They've been
in your closet this whole time.

205
00:22:57,640 --> 00:22:58,560
What?

206
00:23:00,640 --> 00:23:02,200
Wait, Fun.

207
00:23:03,320 --> 00:23:04,200
What are you doing?

208
00:23:04,280 --> 00:23:05,840
That's my closet.

209
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:07,520
Mine is full.

210
00:23:08,320 --> 00:23:11,720
You have one, two, three, four, five…

211
00:23:12,360 --> 00:23:15,720
five closets and they're all full?
I only have two.

212
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:18,160
And they're not full yet.
There's still space.

213
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:24,360
Oon-oon, you decide, what should we eat?

214
00:23:25,960 --> 00:23:27,000
Me?

215
00:23:28,640 --> 00:23:31,400
I'm easy. I can eat anything.

216
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:34,280
Alright, how about BBQ?

217
00:23:34,360 --> 00:23:36,920
No, my hair will smell. I just washed it.

218
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:38,360
Then shabu?

219
00:23:38,440 --> 00:23:40,280
No, I don't want anything hot.

220
00:23:40,960 --> 00:23:42,360
I just saw a doctor.

221
00:23:42,440 --> 00:23:43,720
Steak, then?

222
00:23:43,800 --> 00:23:45,600
We just had that yesterday.

223
00:23:48,320 --> 00:23:51,840
"I'm easy. I can eat anything."

224
00:23:51,920 --> 00:23:54,000
Yeah, so easy.

225
00:24:00,480 --> 00:24:03,080
Good afternoon, girls!

226
00:24:03,160 --> 00:24:07,240
Wait, hold on. Let's chat a bit.

227
00:24:07,320 --> 00:24:08,360
Alright.

228
00:24:11,840 --> 00:24:14,160
- Hello.
- Hello, Aunt Wi.

229
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:16,600
Thank you
for watering the plants yesterday.

230
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:18,480
Oh, never mind.

231
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:22,680
Your house is like mine, and mine
is like yours. No need to be shy.

232
00:24:22,760 --> 00:24:24,640
So where are you going on your day off?

233
00:24:24,720 --> 00:24:27,840
We're going out to eat.
Do you want anything?

234
00:24:27,920 --> 00:24:29,760
Oh, no, I don't need anything.

235
00:24:29,840 --> 00:24:32,600
At first, I thought you weren't home.
I didn't see your car.

236
00:24:32,680 --> 00:24:33,680
Oh,

237
00:24:33,760 --> 00:24:36,320
I sent it to get repainted.
It should be back in a couple of days.

238
00:24:36,400 --> 00:24:39,760
Alright then, go ahead.
Go to the restaurant, enjoy yourselves.

239
00:24:39,840 --> 00:24:41,440
I'll watch the house for you.

240
00:24:41,520 --> 00:24:43,920
- Okay.
- Alright.

241
00:24:50,520 --> 00:24:52,240
You're looking at my beauty mark, right?

242
00:24:52,920 --> 00:24:54,720
Yes, it's mine.

243
00:24:54,800 --> 00:24:56,480
It's a lucky one.

244
00:24:56,560 --> 00:24:59,400
This one helps
with intelligence and awareness.

245
00:24:59,480 --> 00:25:02,000
There are so many call center scams,
so I have to wear it.

246
00:25:02,080 --> 00:25:03,480
Oh.

247
00:25:03,560 --> 00:25:05,160
You can go now.

248
00:25:08,360 --> 00:25:09,400
Alright.

249
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:10,440
Go, go.

250
00:25:18,440 --> 00:25:20,640
Papaya salad with fermented fish, please.

251
00:25:21,440 --> 00:25:23,000
Corn salad.

252
00:25:23,080 --> 00:25:25,760
Fried chicken wings. Grilled pork neck.

253
00:25:25,840 --> 00:25:28,440
And spicy pork rib soup.

254
00:25:29,600 --> 00:25:30,760
Do you want anything else?

255
00:25:31,360 --> 00:25:33,440
Nope.

256
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:38,840
That's all.

257
00:25:43,880 --> 00:25:45,200
Hey, Oon-oon.

258
00:25:45,280 --> 00:25:46,680
After we eat,

259
00:25:46,760 --> 00:25:50,000
can I go check out
the shoe shop on the corner?

260
00:25:50,760 --> 00:25:55,000
I've wanted a pair from there for so long,
and I saw there's a 30% sale.

261
00:25:56,240 --> 00:25:57,200
Of course.

262
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:03,480
Actually, you don't even have to wait
for a sale. You can just buy them.

263
00:26:04,080 --> 00:26:06,160
No, I have to ask you first.

264
00:26:08,960 --> 00:26:11,920
Fun, I already told you.

265
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:15,520
You're in charge of all the finances.

266
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:21,720
If you want to buy something,
you can decide. You don't have to ask me.

267
00:26:24,880 --> 00:26:26,800
What if…

268
00:26:27,560 --> 00:26:30,000
I spend it all? What will you do then?

269
00:26:33,200 --> 00:26:35,800
I believe I know you well enough.

270
00:26:43,280 --> 00:26:44,440
Thank you.

271
00:27:00,800 --> 00:27:01,960
Oon-oon.

272
00:27:02,560 --> 00:27:03,560
Yes?

273
00:27:03,640 --> 00:27:06,960
I told you to not forget to wipe your feet
before stepping into the dry area.

274
00:27:07,040 --> 00:27:08,760
It's slippery.

275
00:27:08,840 --> 00:27:09,840
Oh.

276
00:27:11,360 --> 00:27:12,720
I'll clean it.

277
00:27:13,320 --> 00:27:14,480
No need.

278
00:27:21,960 --> 00:27:23,160
And this.

279
00:27:24,760 --> 00:27:28,920
I don't understand.
Why is the sleeve sticking out?

280
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:31,000
Just open the lid and put it inside.

281
00:27:31,080 --> 00:27:33,600
That's it. What's so hard?

282
00:27:35,760 --> 00:27:37,320
It's not hard.

283
00:27:46,400 --> 00:27:47,440
The toothpaste?

284
00:27:49,560 --> 00:27:52,520
How many times do I have to tell you
to close the cap, or it'll dry out?

285
00:28:22,840 --> 00:28:24,080
You're putting it there?

286
00:28:27,920 --> 00:28:30,800
I'm putting… putting…

287
00:28:30,880 --> 00:28:32,360
putting…

288
00:28:34,480 --> 00:28:35,760
Here.

289
00:28:38,560 --> 00:28:40,240
I'll put toothpaste on your brush.

290
00:29:01,320 --> 00:29:04,200
Can I take this?

291
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:07,320
Go ahead.

292
00:29:32,520 --> 00:29:33,800
Fun.

293
00:29:34,600 --> 00:29:36,480
Can you leave the curtains open a little?

294
00:29:36,560 --> 00:29:39,760
I like when the morning light comes in.
It feels refreshing.

295
00:29:47,040 --> 00:29:49,080
A little more.

296
00:29:53,640 --> 00:29:54,840
Is this enough?

297
00:29:57,920 --> 00:30:00,680
That's perfect.

298
00:30:07,160 --> 00:30:08,120
Thank you.

299
00:30:09,160 --> 00:30:10,320
Sure.

300
00:30:15,840 --> 00:30:18,280
Oon-oon,
what temperature is the AC? It's cold.

301
00:30:27,360 --> 00:30:29,040
Twenty-three.

302
00:30:29,120 --> 00:30:32,120
That's too cold. Twenty-five is enough.

303
00:30:32,640 --> 00:30:35,320
Come on, Fun.

304
00:30:36,440 --> 00:30:38,240
That's too warm.

305
00:30:38,320 --> 00:30:42,280
Oon, I gave in about the curtains.

306
00:30:43,800 --> 00:30:46,720
Let's meet in the middle, 24.

307
00:30:48,600 --> 00:30:50,600
- Twenty-five.
- Alright, twenty-four.

308
00:30:59,800 --> 00:31:01,240
I'll turn off the lights now.

309
00:31:02,040 --> 00:31:02,880
Okay.

310
00:31:15,720 --> 00:31:16,880
Did you forget something?

311
00:31:17,560 --> 00:31:19,840
Forget what?

312
00:31:19,920 --> 00:31:23,000
Lights off, water off, plugs unplugged.

313
00:31:24,080 --> 00:31:25,160
Nothing.

314
00:31:32,120 --> 00:31:34,120
I know what I forgot.

315
00:31:37,760 --> 00:31:39,120
Good night.

316
00:31:39,720 --> 00:31:42,040
My dreams are already good.

317
00:31:42,960 --> 00:31:46,480
I'm cute, I'm always right.

318
00:31:49,320 --> 00:31:50,440
Good night.

319
00:32:04,200 --> 00:32:05,200
Good night.

320
00:32:06,320 --> 00:32:07,520
Good night.

321
00:32:34,880 --> 00:32:35,840
Sorry.

322
00:32:40,200 --> 00:32:42,280
Fun, do you smell something sour?

323
00:32:47,120 --> 00:32:48,480
Oh.

324
00:32:49,320 --> 00:32:51,920
Found it. It's mine.

325
00:32:54,120 --> 00:32:56,120
- Pafun.
- Stop.

326
00:32:56,800 --> 00:32:59,280
It's okay. I'll throw it away.

327
00:33:11,280 --> 00:33:14,520
Do you know that the smell of spoiled
things can stay in the car for hours?

328
00:33:14,600 --> 00:33:17,200
- And if we don't--
- I know, I know.

329
00:33:17,280 --> 00:33:18,520
It's my fault.

330
00:33:18,600 --> 00:33:21,080
From now on,
if I bring anything to eat in the car,

331
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:23,280
I won't forget to throw it away again.

332
00:33:24,560 --> 00:33:28,200
- I said--
- Can you not rub it in? I was wrong.

333
00:33:29,120 --> 00:33:32,520
It's a workday morning.
We should stay cheerful.

334
00:33:32,600 --> 00:33:34,720
Do you want me to feel down?

335
00:33:34,800 --> 00:33:36,480
What if I can't work properly

336
00:33:36,560 --> 00:33:39,920
and get fired? Is that what you want?

337
00:33:41,320 --> 00:33:42,880
Huh?

338
00:33:44,600 --> 00:33:48,960
I… don't think it's that serious.

339
00:33:56,360 --> 00:33:58,520
Let's go to work, alright?

340
00:33:58,600 --> 00:33:59,480
Come here.

341
00:34:10,280 --> 00:34:13,360
Stay cheerful.

342
00:34:47,800 --> 00:34:50,320
Hey, Pafun, Opal.

343
00:34:52,800 --> 00:34:55,600
Why does it feel like
we never see each other anymore?

344
00:34:56,239 --> 00:34:59,920
Well, we've been working from home lately,
and I've been on-site a lot.

345
00:35:00,800 --> 00:35:04,040
Hey, did you hear?
There's a new wall design.

346
00:35:04,760 --> 00:35:07,120
{\an8}New wall? Hold on.

347
00:35:07,640 --> 00:35:10,640
{\an8}Pause the work for now. Let me talk
about something more important.

348
00:35:10,720 --> 00:35:12,360
The new clothing collection is out.

349
00:35:12,440 --> 00:35:14,080
{\an8}- Let me see. The colors are nice.
- Look.

350
00:35:14,160 --> 00:35:16,120
{\an8}Very Pantone-perfect. Here.

351
00:35:17,680 --> 00:35:19,680
- That's stunning.
- Very lovely.

352
00:35:19,760 --> 00:35:21,880
- Very trendy.
- Or should we just get the real thing?

353
00:35:21,960 --> 00:35:24,320
{\an8}Have you submitted your reports?

354
00:35:28,440 --> 00:35:29,360
Peter.

355
00:35:29,440 --> 00:35:31,160
All done, Peter.

356
00:35:31,240 --> 00:35:33,880
Yes, just uploading now, Peter.

357
00:35:35,240 --> 00:35:39,040
And yours, Pafun?
Mr. Sansuk's house project, is it done?

358
00:35:39,640 --> 00:35:40,680
Almost finished.

359
00:35:40,760 --> 00:35:43,840
Just a few final details,
then the client can inspect it.

360
00:35:44,560 --> 00:35:48,320
Also, I'm bidding on the housing project,
just like in the report I submitted.

361
00:35:49,680 --> 00:35:51,360
Peter, look.

362
00:35:51,440 --> 00:35:53,200
This collection even has baby items.

363
00:35:53,280 --> 00:35:56,600
The colors are so cute.

364
00:35:56,680 --> 00:35:58,640
Every color looks great, Peter.

365
00:35:58,720 --> 00:36:01,720
- You should just buy the whole collection.
- Seriously.

366
00:36:02,760 --> 00:36:03,600
Is it expensive?

367
00:36:03,680 --> 00:36:04,920
Not at all.

368
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:07,640
- Just get the whole set.
- Yes, just get everything.

369
00:36:07,720 --> 00:36:10,320
Look, so adorable. And look at this part.

370
00:36:10,400 --> 00:36:11,560
It's nice.

371
00:36:11,640 --> 00:36:12,800
Here.

372
00:36:12,880 --> 00:36:14,480
This color looks nice.

373
00:36:14,560 --> 00:36:16,640
Such a cheerful morning.

374
00:36:20,960 --> 00:36:23,400
That's all for today's details.

375
00:36:23,480 --> 00:36:26,440
As for the remaining points and revisions,

376
00:36:26,520 --> 00:36:28,200
we'll schedule another meeting.

377
00:36:29,800 --> 00:36:33,480
Ms. Nan, please coordinate
the details with Nu.

378
00:36:34,080 --> 00:36:35,120
Sure.

379
00:36:35,200 --> 00:36:36,160
Thank you.

380
00:36:42,440 --> 00:36:43,960
{\an8}- Oon.
- Hmm?

381
00:36:44,040 --> 00:36:48,240
{\an8}I heard something, but it hasn't been
confirmed yet. There's a foreign investor

382
00:36:48,320 --> 00:36:51,160
planning to build a condo
in the city center.

383
00:36:52,400 --> 00:36:53,640
Is it our company's project?

384
00:36:53,720 --> 00:36:54,600
Yeah.

385
00:36:55,720 --> 00:36:58,240
The current workload
is already overwhelming.

386
00:36:58,320 --> 00:37:00,360
I just finished the dimension summary.

387
00:37:00,880 --> 00:37:03,800
Just hearing that gave me a headache.
Same here.

388
00:37:03,880 --> 00:37:07,320
My design still hasn't been finalized
with the owner. It keeps getting revised.

389
00:37:07,400 --> 00:37:11,160
Then let's leave it to the future.

390
00:37:11,760 --> 00:37:13,960
Let's focus on finishing
our current projects first.

391
00:37:14,040 --> 00:37:15,040
Yeah.

392
00:37:16,560 --> 00:37:20,320
Any plans after work?
Are you going anywhere?

393
00:37:21,680 --> 00:37:23,720
Not really, but I need to pick up Fun.

394
00:37:24,480 --> 00:37:26,640
Her car's in the paint shop.

395
00:37:27,600 --> 00:37:30,040
Alright. Don't say I didn't invite you.

396
00:37:30,120 --> 00:37:31,320
I'm going now.

397
00:37:32,240 --> 00:37:33,160
See you.

398
00:37:46,880 --> 00:37:49,560
Fun, you can go shower first.

399
00:37:49,640 --> 00:37:51,560
I just need to finish a little more work.

400
00:37:53,120 --> 00:37:54,520
Want me to warm up the pad thai?

401
00:37:56,240 --> 00:37:57,560
Maybe not yet.

402
00:38:01,960 --> 00:38:06,000
I don't have to go to the office tomorrow.
No need to leave extra time for me.

403
00:38:06,080 --> 00:38:07,360
Okay.

404
00:39:03,400 --> 00:39:04,840
You still haven't eaten the pad thai?

405
00:39:05,840 --> 00:39:07,160
Not yet.

406
00:39:07,240 --> 00:39:09,520
Let me finish a little more work first.

407
00:39:25,560 --> 00:39:27,160
Why don't you go sleep upstairs?

408
00:39:55,160 --> 00:39:56,280
Oon.

409
00:39:58,720 --> 00:40:01,520
Oon, it's morning.

410
00:40:02,920 --> 00:40:05,520
Wake up. Oon.

411
00:40:08,360 --> 00:40:09,280
It's morning already.

412
00:40:20,600 --> 00:40:23,600
- Have you been that busy lately?
- Yes.

413
00:40:24,200 --> 00:40:27,320
I have to finalize the structural
standards and send them to the owner.

414
00:40:29,440 --> 00:40:31,760
Oh, let me hurry and take a shower first.

415
00:40:32,680 --> 00:40:35,960
- Then I'll prepare breakfast for you.
- It's okay.

416
00:40:36,560 --> 00:40:39,440
I probably won't have time to eat.
Thank you, though.

417
00:40:55,080 --> 00:40:59,560
RECIPE

418
00:41:02,080 --> 00:41:04,080
INGREDIENTS

419
00:41:04,160 --> 00:41:06,840
OLIVE OIL, OREGANO

420
00:41:06,920 --> 00:41:08,600
SALT, BLACK PEPPER

421
00:41:58,480 --> 00:41:59,520
Yes, Fun?

422
00:41:59,600 --> 00:42:01,360
How's work today?

423
00:42:02,160 --> 00:42:05,400
It's fine. I submitted it already.
It's not too hectic anymore.

424
00:42:07,920 --> 00:42:12,880
Aioon, after work today,
come straight home. We need to talk.

425
00:42:15,840 --> 00:42:17,520
About what?

426
00:42:18,480 --> 00:42:21,200
Let's talk when you get home. That's all.

427
00:42:22,480 --> 00:42:23,520
Huh?

428
00:42:28,520 --> 00:42:29,560
What did I do wrong?

429
00:42:31,040 --> 00:42:32,040
Breakfast?

430
00:42:33,160 --> 00:42:35,160
Or did I forget
to close the toothpaste again?

431
00:42:36,520 --> 00:42:37,760
Probably not.

432
00:42:51,960 --> 00:42:53,560
INCOMING CALL - MOM

433
00:42:57,240 --> 00:42:58,440
Yes, Mom?

434
00:42:58,520 --> 00:43:00,000
<i>Oon, where are you?</i>

435
00:43:01,400 --> 00:43:03,600
On the road. I'm heading home.

436
00:43:03,680 --> 00:43:08,040
I'm in Bangkok for Aunt Kaew's funeral.

437
00:43:08,120 --> 00:43:11,840
<i>I want you to come pick me up</i>
<i>around 7:00 at Wat Dokmai.</i>

438
00:43:11,920 --> 00:43:14,680
And tonight,
I'm going to stay at your house.

439
00:43:14,760 --> 00:43:16,080
Huh?

440
00:43:16,160 --> 00:43:17,480
<i>Huh what?</i>

441
00:43:17,560 --> 00:43:19,200
Why? Can't I stay at your house?

442
00:43:19,840 --> 00:43:22,520
No, you can. Of course you can.

443
00:43:22,600 --> 00:43:24,560
Then hurry up and come get me.

444
00:43:24,640 --> 00:43:25,480
<i>Okay.</i>

445
00:43:29,920 --> 00:43:30,760
MOM

446
00:43:33,480 --> 00:43:34,560
PAFUN

447
00:43:34,640 --> 00:43:35,840
NU (BOSS)

448
00:43:38,800 --> 00:43:39,880
Yes, Nu?

449
00:44:10,840 --> 00:44:14,080
OON-OON

450
00:44:31,720 --> 00:44:32,640
Mom.

451
00:44:34,440 --> 00:44:38,280
Why are you carrying that yourself?
Why didn't you wait for me?

452
00:44:38,360 --> 00:44:40,280
Because you were taking forever.

453
00:44:40,800 --> 00:44:43,400
You know your back hurts,
and you're still being stubborn.

454
00:44:43,480 --> 00:44:46,080
Tomorrow, let's go to the hospital.
I'll take you myself.

455
00:44:47,240 --> 00:44:49,160
Don't make such a big deal out of it.

456
00:44:49,240 --> 00:44:52,000
If I really can't manage,
I'll go by myself.

457
00:46:56,920 --> 00:46:58,440
{\an8}Hello.

458
00:47:00,200 --> 00:47:01,760
{\an8}I've been thinking about this for a while.

459
00:47:01,840 --> 00:47:04,840
{\an8}I want you to move into a retirement home.

460
00:47:05,640 --> 00:47:07,520
{\an8}Fun, no!

461
00:47:07,600 --> 00:47:08,520
{\an8}‪Mom!

462
00:47:08,600 --> 00:47:11,720
{\an8}Fun, why weren't you more careful?
You know Mom's back hurts.

463
00:47:11,800 --> 00:47:12,800
{\an8}I'm coming with you, Oon.

464
00:47:12,880 --> 00:47:13,880
{\an8}No need.

465
00:47:13,960 --> 00:47:16,280
{\an8}<i>Maybe we're really going to break up.</i>

466
00:47:16,360 --> 00:47:18,360
{\an8}Oon has never raised her voice at me.

467
00:47:18,440 --> 00:47:20,520
{\an8}You should value yourself

468
00:47:20,600 --> 00:47:23,720
{\an8}<i>and walk away from that person's life.</i>

469
00:47:54,320 --> 00:47:56,520
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon

